Cuerpo: Date: Tue, 26 Nov 1996 23:18:04 GMT Server: Apache/1.1.1 Content-type: text/html ISU, Department of Computer Science Computing activities began at Iowa State in the late 1930's when John Vincent Atanasoff , a professor of physics and mathematics, built a computer on campus that is now recognized as the first electronic digital computer. The Department of Computer Science was established as a formal discipline in 1969, offering from the outset the B.S., M.S. and Ph.D. degrees. The department now has more than 2,200 alumni.
